<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They recently made a comeback to screens with the latest edition of The Mummy Diaries.</p>

<p>And Billie and Sam Faiers appeared to celebrate their return to TV by enjoying a night out at The Arts Club in the English capital on Saturday.</p>

<p>Proving to be in good company, the reality stars, aged 30 and 29 respectively, were joined by close pal Claudia Allen, who recently welcomed a baby with Tony Knightley - the brother of Sam's partner Paul Knightley.</p>

<p>Girls just wanna have fun: Billie (pictured) and Sam Faiers appeared to celebrate their Mummy Diaries return to TV by enjoying a night out at The Arts Club in the English capital on Saturday</p>

<p>Former TOWIE star Billie - who shares Nelly, six, and Arthur, three, with husband Paul Shepherd - looked sensational in a black jumpsuit, which accentuated her slender figure.</p>

<p>Standing out, the mum-of-two boosted her frame in platform heels and carried her essentials in a gold, crocodile skin clutch.</p>

<p>The former glamour model styled her tresses into a high ponytail, while her complexion was enhanced with dewy make-up.  </p>

<p>Sam, meanwhile, exuded sophistication in brown co-ords, complete with a baggy satin shirt and matching trousers. </p>

